    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "So to tackle the \"update the data\" case. What we could do is this:\n\n``` js\ntemplate: function(data, hoganTemplateFn) {\n  var newData = data.map()..\n  return hoganTemplateFn(data)\n}\n```\n\nSo the \"trick\" is to send the default hogan templating function when we get a function as a template. This way the user can reformat the data and still use the default hogan templating system.\n\nThoughts @algolia/javascript ?\n",
