    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "@pixelastic \n\n> Maybe just wait for the need on other widgets before merging?\n\nI have one! Right now, I'm using an optional  `displayFunction` for my facets. It is actually only used in one case of weirdly formatted data : price ranges, but could be needed with other types of attributes.\n\nI'm not found of modifying the data within the `template` function, because to me we should just expect a template to be returned here, not potential data modification.\n\nOn the other hand, I really like the `transformData` idea of a callback to call just before the template rendering. We're always passing an object when rendering a Hogan template, so we would always have the same prototype.\n\nTo me, this:\n\n``` js\n{\n  transformData: function (hit) {\n    return { name: hit.first_name + ' ' + hit.last_name };\n  },\n  template: '{{ name }}'\n}\n```\n\nmakes more sense than this:\n\n``` js\n{\n  template: function(hit, mustacheTemplateFn) {\n    return mustacheTemplateFn('{{ name }}', { name: hit.first_name + ' ' + hit.last_name; });\n  }\n}\n```\n",
